Configuration for this Container's layout. Example:

    @example
    Ext.create({
        xtype: 'container',
        layout: {
            type: 'hbox',
            align: 'middle'
        },
        items: [{
            xtype: 'panel',
            flex: 1,
            bodyStyle: {
                background: "#000",
                color:"#fff"
            }
        }, {
           xtype: 'panel',
           flex: 2,
           bodyStyle: {
               background: "#f00",
               color:"#fff"
           }
        }]
    });

The calendar views to have available, each item in this configuration
(labelled by a key) is to contain the configuration for the view, a class that
extends {@link Ext.calendar.panel.Base}.

Example with a day and week view:

    views: {
        day: {
            xtype: 'calendar-day'
        },
        week: {
            xtype: 'calendar-week'
        }
    }

The "day" and "week" keys would be the eligible values for the
{@link #cfg!defaultView #cfg-defaultView} and the param string to pass to
{@link #method!setView #method-setView}.
